The paper deals with the duality between algebraic and coalgebraic recognition of languages, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and logic. The use of boolean algebras, pseudovarieties, and vector spaces over the binary field suggests connections to topics such as logic, algebra, and linear algebra. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
